Sheffield United could be fined for their late arrival at Tottenham which delayed the start of the first leg of their Capital One Cup semi-final.

United were delayed by bad traffic from their pre-match hotel in North London – and the Football League have written to South Yorkshire club for a formal explanation of how it happened.

Competition rules state team-sheets must be handed to the referee by the manager and captain no later than 75 minutes before scheduled kick-off.

